What is python?
python is an interpreted, object-oriented, high-level programming language that can b used for a wide variety of applications.
python is a powerful general-purpose programming language.
python is open-source programming language.

Features of python

simple & Easy to learn -> clear syntax similar to English
example: if you are creating some kind of website, the syntax is same for programing languages

Interpreted Language -> No compilation needed; run line by line
example: if you are current line is having error it will not execute, you can use debug menu and can easily fix it.
another example if you are having 6 lines of code, and the error is at the line 6th line, the 5 lines of code will execute
but error will be shown at the 6th lines you can easily fix it using debugger. it will not execute if there is any error

Note: not like other languages java or .net first we need to compile and run to check the error.

High level language -> Handle memory management and complex details
example: while talking about plask and django, i want to create ecomm related system and i want to store data in database realate system,
everything can be applicable into highlevelprograming langage

Portable -> Runs on windows, Mac, Linux etc.

Extensive Standard Library -> Comes with built-in modules and functions

Supports Multiple Paradims -> Procedural, Object-Oriented and Functional Programming

Large Community Support -> Easy to find help, tutorials, and libraries